text: Antidesma puncticulatum, known as mao luang, is a species of plant in the family Phyllanthaceae. It was previously classified as a genus within family Euphorbiaceae, but later moved into family Phyllanthaceae. It is native to South Asia and South-east Asian countries. ==References== * Philippine plants * jstor.org * In vitro culturing Category:Flora of Sri Lanka puncticulatum
title: Antidesma puncticulatum
